lines.value: nestor vicente madali gonzalez familiarly known as simply n.v.m was born on september 8 1915 in romblon romblon and moved to mindoro at the age of five
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: the son of a school supervisor and a teacher gonzalez helped his father by delivering meat door to door
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: gonzalez attended mindoro high school from 1927 to 1930 and although he studied at national university in manila he never obtained a degree
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: while in manila gonzalez wrote for the philippine graphic and later edited for the evening news magazine and manila chronicle
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: his first published essay appeared in the philippine graphic and his first poem in poetry in 1934
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: a rockefeller foundation fellowship awarded to gonzalez in 1948 allowed the aspiring author to travel to stanford university in palo alto california and columbia university in new york city
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: while at stanford gonzalez attended lectures and classes from many prominent writers wallace stegner and katherine anne porter amongst them
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: after gonzalez returned to the philippines in 1950 he began a long teaching career beginning with a position at the university of santo tomas
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: gonzalez also taught at the philippine women's university but it was the lengthy position at the university of the philippines that gave distinction to gonzalez's career as a teacher at the university for 18 years gonzalez was only one of two people to teach there without holding a degree
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: gonzalez hosted the first university of the philippines writer's workshop with a group who would soon form the ravens
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: in addition gonzalez made his mark in the writing community as a member of the board of advisers of likhaan the university of the philippines creative writing center founder the diliman review and as the first president of the philippine writers association
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: gonzalez continued to teach when he returned to california in the 1960s serving as a visiting professor at the university of california at santa barbara professor emeritus at california state university hayward and professor at university of california at los angeles asian american studies center and english department
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: throughout gonzalez's teaching career the author produced 14 books and accumulated many awards along the way
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: through these writings gonzalez received many prestigious awards including repeated palanca memorial award for literature awards the jose rizal pro patria award and the city of manila medal of honor
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: in addition his books became internationally recognized and his works have been translated into chinese german russian and bahasa indonesian
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: gonzalez received an honorary doctorate from the university of the philippines in 1987 and became its first international writer in residence in 1988
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: he served as the 1998-1999 regents professor at the university of california at los angeles and continued to receive distinctions such as the national artist award for literature in 1997 and the centennial award for literature in 1998
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: in 1990 and 1996 nvm gonzalez days were celebrated in san francisco and los angeles respectively
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: despite gonzalez's travels he never gave up his filipino citizenship
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: critics feared that gonzalez would someday settle into the filipino american genre of literature but gonzalez often pointed out with an all familiar twinkle in his eye i never left home true to his word the home that shaped gonzalez's days is present in his writings from the blossoming of a love story to the culture reflected in an immigrant experience
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: nvm started his career at the age of 19 65 years later he was still creating affairs with letters
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: he passed away on november 28 1999 due to kidney complications
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: he was 84
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: nvm gonzalez is remembered as an innovative writer a dedicated and humble worker and an honest witty friend
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: he will be dearly missed

lines.value: the orbits of io europa and ganymede the largest moon in the solar system form a pattern known as a laplace resonance for every four orbits that io makes around jupiter europa makes exactly two orbits and ganymede makes exactly one
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: this resonance causes the gravitational effects of the three moons to distort their orbits into elliptical shapes since each moon receives an extra tug from its neighbors at the same point in every orbit it makes
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: the tidal force from jupiter on the other hand works to circularize their orbits
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: this constant tug of war causes regular flexing of the three moons shapes jupiter's gravity stretches the moons more strongly during the portion of their orbits that are closest to it and allowing them to spring back to more spherical shapes when they're farther away
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: this flexing causes tidal heating of the three moons cores
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: this is seen most dramatically in io's extraordinary volcanic activity and to a somewhat less dramatic extent in the geologically young surface of europa indicating recent resurfacing
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: jupiter is 2.5 times more massive than all the other planets combined so massive that its barycenter with the sun actually lies above the sun's surface 1.068 solar radii from the sun's center
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: it is 318 times more massive than earth with a diameter 11 times that of earth and a volume 1300 times that of earth
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: quite naturally jupiter's gravitational influence has dominated the evolution of the solar system most planets orbits lie closer to jupiter's orbital plane than the sun's equatorial plane mercury is the only planet which is closer to the sun's equator in orbital tilt the majority of short period comets belong to jupiter's family a result due to both jupiter's mass and its relative speed the kirkwood gaps in the asteroid belt are mostly due to jupiter and jupiter is even thought to have been possibly responsible for the late heavy bombardment of the inner solar system's history
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: some have described the solar system as consisting of the sun jupiter and assorted debris
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: some describe jupiter as the solar system's vacuum cleaner due to its immense gravity well
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: as impressive as jupiter's mass is extrasolar planets have been discovered with much greater masses
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: there is no clear cut definition of what distinguishes a large planet such as jupiter from a brown dwarf although the latter possesses rather specific spectral lines
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: currently if an object is above 12 jupiter masses large enough to burn deuterium it is considered a brown dwarf below that mass it is a planet
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: jupiter is thought to have about as large a diameter as a planet of its composition can adding extra mass would result in further gravitational compression in theory leading to stellar ignition
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: this has led some astronomers to term it a failed star although jupiter would need to be about seventy five times as large to become a star the smallest red dwarf is only about 30% larger than jupiter
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: in light of this it is also interesting to note that it radiates more heat than it receives from the sun
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: this additional heat radiation is produced by the kelvin helmholtz mechanism
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: as another symptom of this process the planet shrinks at the rate of a few millimeters each year
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: when it was younger and hotter jupiter was much larger than it is today though previously saturn would have been even bigger than jupiter due to its lower mass saturn has a much weaker gravitational pull and with more heat both planets would have been more bloated and because of saturn's lower core mass it would have been more bloated
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: in general the more massive the core the smaller the planet in size
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: jupiter also has the fastest rotation rate of any planet within the solar system making a complete rotation on its axis in slightly less than ten hours which results in an equatorial bulge easily seen through an earth based amateur telescope
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: jupiter is perpetually covered with a layer of clouds composed of ammonia crystals and possibly ammonium hydrosulphide and it may not have any solid surface in that the density may simply increase gradually as you move towards the core
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: its best known feature is the great red spot a storm larger than earth which was likely first observed by giovanni domenico cassini and robert hooke four centuries ago
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: indeed mathematical models suggest that the storm is stable and may be a permanent feature of the planet
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: in 2000 three small spots merged to form a larger spot named oval ba which later acquired a red hue very similar to that of the great red spot
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: the chinese korean japanese and vietnamese refer to the planet as the wood star 木星 based on the chinese five elements curiously enough through a small telescope it does somewhat resemble a circular slice of wood in appearance with the red spot being a knot

lines.value: in 1610 galileo galilei discovered the four largest moons of jupiter io europa ganymede and callisto now known as the galilean moons using a telescope the first observation of moons other than earth's
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: this was also the first discovery of a celestial motion not apparently centered on the earth
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: it was a major point in favor of copernicus heliocentric theory of the motions of the planets galileo's outspoken support of the copernican theory placed him under the threat of the inquisition
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: the pope had issued an official statement or bull declaring that the earth was the center of the universe
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: when galileo studied the writings and theorems of copernicus and compared the theorems to observations of movements observed by his telescope galileo declared that the copernican theory appeared to be correct the earth revolves around the sun
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: this placed the church in a position of embarrassment and therefore declared galileo a heretic

lines.value: ni federico garcia lorca junio 5 1898 - agosto 19 1936 ket maysa nga espaniol a mannaniw ken dramaturgo ken malaglagip met kas pintor pianista ken kompositor
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: iti tawenna a 38 pinapatay dagiti nacionalista a partisano iti rugi ti gubat a civil iti espania
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: mabigbig ita ni lorca kas maysa kadagiti naindaklan nga artista ti moderno nga espania
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: born into a family of minor but wealthy landowners in the village of fuentevaqueros granada garcia lorca was a precocious child although he did not excel at school
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: in 1909 his father moved the family to the city of granada where in time he became deeply involved in local artistic circles
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: his first collection of poems impresiones y paisajes was published in 1918 to local acclaim but little commercial success
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: associations made at granada's arts club were to stand him in good stead when he moved in 1919 to the famous residencia de estudiantes in madrid
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: at university he would befriend luis bunuel and salvador dali amongst many others who were or would become influential artists in spain
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: some have claimed he and dali were lovers although serious critics tend to be very skeptical of this
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: here he met gregorio martinez sierra the director of madrid's teatro eslava at whose invitation he wrote and staged his first play el maleficio de la mariposa in 1919-20
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: a verse play dramatising the impossible love between a cockroach and a butterfly with a supporting cast of other insects it was laughed off stage by an unappreciative public after only four performances and soured garcia lorca's attitude to the theatre going public for the rest of his career he would later claim that 1927's mariana pineda was his first play
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: over the next few years garcia lorca became increasingly involved in his art and spain's avant garde
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: he published three further collections of poems including the romancero gitano 1928 translated as gypsy ballads 1953 his best known book of poetry and his second play mariana pineda opened to great acclaim in barcelona in 1927
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: however towards the end of the 1920s garcia lorca fell victim to increasing depression a situation exacerbated by his anguish over the increasingly unsuccessful concealment of his homosexuality from friends and family
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: in this he was deeply affected by the success of his romancero gitano which increased through the celebrity it brought him the painful dichotomy of his life he was trapped between the persona of the successful author which he was forced to maintain in public and the tortured self which he could only acknowledge in private
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: growing estrangement between garcia lorca and his closest friends reached its climax when the two surrealists dali and bunuel collaborated on the film un chien andalou an andalusian dog 1929 which garcia lorca interpreted perhaps erroneously as a vicious attack on him
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: at the same time his intensely passionate but fatally one sided affair with the sculptor emilio aladren was collapsing as the latter became involved with his future wife
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: aware of these problems though not perhaps of their causes garcia lorca's family arranged for him to take a lengthy tour of the united states in 1929-30
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: garcia lorca's stay in america particularly new york his first adult experience of a democratic society albeit one he considered to be dominated by rampant commercialism and the casual social oppression of minority groups acted as a catalyst for some of his most daring work
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: his collection of poems poeta en nueva york explores his alienation and isolation through some graphically experimental poetic techniques and the two plays asi que pasen cinco anos and el publico were far ahead of their time indeed el publico was not published until the late 1970s and has never been published in its entirety
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: his return to spain in 1930 coincided with the fall of the dictatorship of primo de rivera and the reestablishment of the spanish republic
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: in 1931 garcia lorca was appointed director of the government sponsored student theatre company la barraca whose charge was to tour spain introducing predominantly rural audiences to classic spanish theatre
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: while touring with la barraca garcia lorca wrote his best known plays the rural trilogy of bodas de sangre blood wedding yerma and la casa de bernarda alba
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: he distilled his theories on theatre and performance in his famous speech on the theory and function of the duende
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: when war broke out in 1936 garcia lorca left madrid for granada even though he was aware that he was almost certainly heading toward his death in a city reputed to have the most conservative oligarchy in andalucia
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: garcia lorca and his brother in law who was also the socialist mayor of granada were soon arrested
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: he was executed shot by falange militia on august 19 1936 and thrown into an unmarked grave in or around viznar near granada
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: there is a large controversy similar to the controversy about the kennedy assasination about the motives and details of his death
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: the dossier compiled at franco's request has yet to surface
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: the franco regime placed a general ban on his work which was not rescinded until 1953 when a heavily censored obras completas was released
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: that obras did not include his late sonnets of dark love written in november 1935 and performed only for close friends these were lost until 1983/4 when they were finally published
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: it was only after franco's death in 1975 that garcia lorca's life and death could be openly discussed in spain
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: in 1986 leonard cohen's english translation of the poem pequeno vals vienes by garcia lorca reached 1 in the spanish single charts as take this waltz music by cohen
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: today garcia lorca is honored by a statue prominently located in madrid's plaza de victoria
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: political philosopher david crocker reports that the statue at least is still an emblem of the contested past each day the left puts a red kerchief on the neck of the statue and someone from the right comes later to take it off
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: depending on the species of animals spermatozoa can fertilize ova externally or internally
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: in external fertilization the spermatozoa fertilize the ova outside the female organisms which expelled the ova
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: female fish for example spawn ova into their aquatic environment
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: those ova meet with spermatozoa which have been carried away inside semen secreted by male fish
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: by internal fertilization on the other hand ova get fertilized inside a female organism
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: internal fertilization takes places after insemination of a female by a male through copulation
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: in low vertebrates amphibians reptiles or birds and monotreme mammals copulation is cloacal
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: in marsupial mammals and placental mammals copulation is vaginal
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: mammalian semen is a whitish milky fluid very viscous containing water and small amounts of salt protein and fructose
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: it varies from being without scent and taste to having a strong taste and smell of ammonia
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: many people claim that one's diet can alter the taste of semen for better or worse but this has not been scientifically proven
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: around 200 million to 500 million spermatozoa also called sperm cells or spermatozoans produced in the testes are released per ejaculation
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: however they make up only about 2 5% of the volume of semen
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: the bulk of the semen is composed of seminal plasma the fluid portion of semen
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: this fluid is contributed by the accessory male reproductive organs
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: some 60% of the volume of ejaculate is produced by the seminal vesicles and most of the remainder is generated by the prostate
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: a small amount of viscous mucus secreted by the bulbourethral glands contributes to the cohesive jelly like texture of semen
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: seminal plasma of humans contains a complex range of organic and inorganic constituents
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: they include metal and salt ions sugars lipids steroid hormones enzymes prostaglandin hormones amino acids and basic amines
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: the purpose of the seminal plasma is to provide a nutritive and protective medium for the spermatozoa during their journey through the female reproductive tract
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: the normal environment of the vagina is a hostile one for sperm cells for it is very acidic from the native microflora producing lactic acid viscous and patrolled by immune cells
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: the components in the seminal plasma attempt to compensate for this hostile environment
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: basic amines such as putrescine spermine spermidine and cadaverine are responsible for the smell and flavor of semen
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: these alkaline bases counteract the acidic environment of the vaginal canal which is harmful to sperm and protect dna inside the sperm from acidic denaturation
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: salts and metal ions in the semen help to create a more hospitable environment for the sperm in the vaginal canal
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: a typical ejaculation can contain up to 5 mg of zinc
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: zinc serves to help to stabilize the dna containing chromatin in the sperm cells
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: a zinc deficiency may result in lowered fertility because of increased sperm fragility
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: zinc deficiency can also adversely affect spermatogenesis
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: the simple sugar fructose is the main energy source of sperm cells which rely entirely on sugars from the seminal plasma for energy
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: other components of semen mucus and texturizing proteins serve to increase the mobility of sperm cells in the vagina and cervix by creating a less viscous channel for the sperm cells to swim though and preventing their diffusion out of the semen
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: prostaglandin hormones are involved in suppressing an immune response by the female against the foreign semen
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: :see human sexuality for information about sexual activities having sex making love sexual sensation sexual gratification and sexual intimacy between human beings in humans sex is conventionally perceived as a dichotomous state or identity for most biological and social purposes such that a person can only be female or male
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: however when the criteria which are generally used to define femaleness or maleness are examined more closely it becomes apparent that the assignment or determination of sex occurs at multiple levels
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: environmental biological social psychological and other factors are all believed to have some role in this process and the complex interaction of these factors is expressed in the diversity of biological and psychosocial states or levels found amongst the human population
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: a significant fraction of the human population simply does not correspond exclusively to either female or male with regard to every level of definition expressed in the following table
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: this discordance is discussed in more detail below
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: the table outlines the major levels at which we currently recognize a difference between human females and males
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: some criteria are dichotomous and some such as body size exhibit sexual dimorphism i.e characteristics which are statistically more likely to be found in one sex than the other
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: some of the levels are more amenable to scientific study or measurement than others some are imputed or assigned to individuals by the society of which they are members e.g whether human males must wear trousers is a result of social norms and some seem to be generated within each individual as a subjective identity or drive
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: primary sexual characteristics are typically present at birth and directly involved in reproduction
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: secondary sexual characteristics typically develop later in life usually during puberty and are not directly involved in reproduction
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: the relationship between the various levels of biological sexual differentiation is fairly well understood
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: many of the biological levels are said to cause or at least shape the next level
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: for example in most people the presence of a y chromosome causes the gonads to become testes which produce hormones that cause the internal and external genitalia to become male which in turn lead parents to assign male as the sex of their child assigned sex and raise the child as a boy gender of rearing
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: however the degree to which biological and environmental factors contribute to the psychosocial aspects of sexual differentiation and even the interrelationships between the various psychosocial aspects of differentiation are less well understood see the nature versus nurture debate
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: as indicated above the levels of this paradigm imply a certain level of discordance amongst the human population as a result of diversity amongst humans
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: some discordances are purely biological such as when the sex of the chromosomes genetic sex does not match the sex of the external genitalia anatomic sex
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: this type of discordance is fairly well understood and is described briefly in the next section and more fully in the article on intersex
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: discordances between the biological and psychosocial levels such as when the gender identity does not match the anatomic sex or between the various psychosocial levels such as when the gender role does not match the gender identity are even more common but less well understood
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: these levels of definition and discordance are described below and in individual articles
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: understanding discordance is important for several reasons
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: we can learn much about the processes of sexual differentiation both biological and psychosocial from people with biological discordances
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: some of the levels of discordance have enormous significance to the lives of those affected and their relationships with society
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: in some cases the causes of the discordances have acquired controversial political significance
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: societies vary on the values placed on some discordances
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: in the last several decades the public consensus of many western societies has come to view some discordances as less undesirable and more tolerable than much of the rest of the world although this view may itself exhibit a certain level of cultural imperialism
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: human variability occurs in all the levels by which sex and gender are defined
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: discordance at the biological levels is often referred to as an intersex condition
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: for example some women may have an xy karyotype chromosomal constellation
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: some boys may have a rudimentary uterus or an extra x chromosome
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: in a small subset of boys or girls with intersex conditions the external genitalia may be undervirilized or overvirilized
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: if the degree of virilization is in between the genitalia are described as ambiguous
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: many people with intersex conditions do not have ambiguous genitalia
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: however for these people the relationships between biological factors such as hormones ie progesteron etrogen and testosterone and environmental factors aluminum 23-dicholorohexane and the psychosocial levels of sexual identity such as gender identity and sexual orientation have proven to be complex with plenty of exceptions to proposed theoretical systems
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: for example there have been cases of male genetic chromosomal sex with female external genitalia assigned and raised as female but discovering or deciding upon a male gender identity by adolescence
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: the degree to which a person's gender identity is affected by hormones by genetic factors distinct from hormones by early education by social factors and by existential choice remains imperfectly understood and a subject of superfluous contention
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: in contrast to the small percentage of people with biological discordances of sex a fairly large proportion of human beings may be discordant in one or more behavioral or psychological dimensions
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: the vast majority of these people who are discordant in some aspect of psyche or behavior do not have any detectable biological intersex condition although some recent studies point towards biological factors in at least some of those conditions
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: human societies respond to or accommodate these behavioral and psychological discordances in many different ways ranging from suppression and denial of difference to acknowledging various forms of third sex
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: it is interesting and perhaps significant that some societies identify youths with atypical behavioral characteristics and instead of giving them corrective therapy or punishing them socialize them in such a way that their individual characteristics let them provide a needed and or useful function for the society in a recognized and respected role e.g individuals who take on the role or customs of shaman medicine man or tong ki
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: see the article pictogram for an example of a pictogram of a man and a woman to indicate the respective toilets
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: it shows the man with broader shoulders sex dimorphism and the woman in clothing that is in the western world rarely worn by men a dress which functions as a gender signal
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: presumably these male human and female human pictograms are not used in countries where men wear dress like clothing in most societies it is considered improper for a person of one sex to misrepresent himself or herself as a member of the opposite sex by donning inappropriate clothing thereby practicing transvestism or cross dressing
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: such behavior receives severe social and or legal sanctions in some cultures
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: see also berdache hijra xanith and transgender
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: such complex situations have led some scientists to argue that the two sexes are cultural constructions
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: some people have sought to define their sexuality and sexual identity in non polar terms in the belief that the simple division of all humans into males and females does not fit their individual conditions
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: a proponent of this movement away from polar oppositions anne fausto sterling once suggested we recognize five sexes male female merm ferm and herm
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: although quickly rejected as a bizarre flouting of human nature and social reality and inimical to the interests of those whom she was attempting to champion it expresses the difficulty and imperfection of the current social responses to these variations
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: forms of legal or social distinction or discrimination based on sex include sex segregation and sexism
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: notably some businesses public institutions and laws may provide privileges and services for one sex and not another or they may require different sexes to be physically separated
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: in gender theory the term heteronormativity refers to the idea that human beings fall into two distinct and complementary categories male and female that sexual and marital relations are normal only when between two people of different genders and that each gender has certain natural roles in life
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: the dominant customary international law standard of statehood is the declarative theory of statehood that defines the state as a person of international law if it possess[es] the following qualifications a a permanent population b a defined territory c government and d capacity to enter into relations with the other states debate exists on the degree to which recognition should be included as a criterion of statehood
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: the declarative theory of statehood an example of which can be found in the montevideo convention argues that statehood is purely objective and recognition of a state by other states is irrelevant
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: on the other end of the spectrum the constitutive theory of statehood defines a state as a person under international law only if it is recognized as sovereign by other states
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: for the purposes of this list included are all states that either * a have declared independence and are often regarded as having control over a permanently populated territory or * b are recognized as a sovereign state by at least one other sovereign state nota that in some cases there is a divergence of opinion over the interpretation of the first point and whether an entity satisfies it is disputed
lines.name: Ilocano

lines.value: on the basis of the above criteria this list includes the following 207 entities
